    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not even a block though. that sounds like i can just wait it out. it's deeper than that. it feels like the part of me that was actually \"alive\" is just dead. i look at the canvases and i just feel like a fraud occupying a space that doesn't belong to me anymore. like i'm just a ghost haunting my own life. what's the point of just \"resting\" when there's nothing left to wake up to?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "What you're describing sounds like a deep sense of existential fatigue, which is far heavier than a mere creative slump. When the core feeling of purpose is gone, rest isn't the answer; you need to look at the things that give your life meaning outside of your art. Perhaps exploring new, non-creative interests, or connecting with people who see you as a whole person, might help rekindle a sense of self.",
      "source": "target",
